state born beauty queen. “We cannot give up on NIGERIA, not now, not ever. Nigeria will be great again and the effort of these heroes will never be in vain”, she added. In the same vein, Queen Vivian announced her new campaign themed ‘NEW NIGERIA’, an initiative open to forge and blend ideas, actions towards a greater forte in the country. Vanguard News Nigeria Tuesday, October 20, 2020 has gone down history globally as a black Tuesday in Nigeria. It was the day Nigerian soldiers opened fire at Nigerian youths who were waving Nigerian flags and singing the Nigerian National Anthem in a peaceful protest against police brutality and organized extortion, a corollary of… November 1, 2020 In "News" …At 6:29pm local time in Lagos, two military vehicles were filmed leaving Bonny Camp …Later footage showed four vehicles with flash lights in a convoy, and they appeared to be vehicles used by the Nigerian military and police. …Same vehicles head east along Ozumba Mbadiwe Avenue, in the direction of… October 29, 2020 In "Headlines" By Gabriel Ewepu - Abuja Joint Nigeria Crisis Action Committee, JN-CAC, and Nigeria Mourns, Thursday, condemned attacks and killings of unarmed and peaceful protesters on Tuesday night at Lekki Toll Plaza in Lagos. This was contained in a statement signed by the conveners, Alu Azege, Abiodun Baiyewu, Benson Olugbuo, Chidi… October 23, 2020 In "News"